## 🔌 Phase 2: Backend API Endpoints Completion

Currently, only `/api/user/me` is wired up. The rest of the routes in [routes.go](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/server/routes/routes.go) are empty.

- [x] **2.1 Implement Project API**
  - [x] Define endpoints in [routes.go](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/server/routes/routes.go#L14):
    - `POST /api/projects` (Create a project) — *Note: `ProjectHandler` currently has `CreateProjectHandler` partially written, need to wire it to the route.*
    - `GET /api/projects` (List user's projects)
    - `DELETE /api/projects/:id` (Delete a project)
  - [x] Update `ProjectService` and `ProjectRepository` to support listing and deleting projects.

- [x] **2.2 Implement Widget API**
  - [x] Define endpoints in [routes.go](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/server/routes/routes.go#L22):
    - `POST /api/widgets` (Create a widget config for a project)
    - `GET /api/widgets/:id` (Public config endpoint for the JS script)
    - `PUT /api/widgets/:id` (Update template, theme, colors, allowed origins, and fields)
    - `DELETE /api/widgets/:id` (Delete a widget)
  - [x] Implement handlers in a new file `widgetHandler.go` under `server/internal/app/handler/`.
  - [x] Create `WidgetService` in a new file `widgetService.go` under `server/internal/app/service/`.

- [x] **2.3 Implement Feedback API**
  - [x] Define endpoints in [routes.go](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/server/routes/routes.go#L18):
    - `POST /api/feedback` (Public endpoint to submit anonymous feedback)
    - `GET /api/feedback` (Authenticated endpoint to list all feedback for user's projects/widgets)
  - [x] Update `FeedbackHandler` ([feedbackHandler.go](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/server/internal/app/handler/feedbackHandler.go)):
    - Add authentication check for `GET /api/feedback`.
    - Adjust request validation to match `api.yaml`.
  - [x] Implement CORS/Allowed Origins validation on the public `POST /api/feedback` endpoint (using the widget configuration's `AllowedOrigins` list to prevent spam from unauthorized domains).

- [x] **2.4 Secure Routes with Auth0 JWT Middleware**
  - [x] Protect all dashboard-facing endpoints (`/api/projects`, authenticated `GET /api/feedback`, and `/api/widgets` management endpoints) using the `JWTMiddleware` defined in [jwt.go](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/server/middleware/jwt.go).

