## 💻 Phase 3: Frontend (Next.js Dashboard) API Integration & Fixes

The frontend is currently relying on mock data and has runtime Next.js navigation bugs.

- [x] **3.1 Fix Next.js Routing Bugs**
  - [x] In [page.tsx](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/dashboard/app/projects/create/page.tsx):
    - Replace `import { useNavigate } from "react-router-dom";` with `import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";`.
    - Change `const navigate = useNavigate();` to `const router = useRouter();`.
    - Update redirection calls from `navigate("/projects")` to `router.push("/projects")`.
  - [x] Remove `react-router-dom` from dependencies in `package.json` to keep the build clean.

- [x] **3.2 Setup Auth0 Routing Handlers**
  - [x] Auth0 is mounted via middleware in v4, no route handler files are required (obsolete handlers removed).
  - [x] Update `Navigation.tsx` ([Navigation.tsx](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/dashboard/components/Navigation.tsx)) to fetch auth state dynamically from Auth0 endpoints instead of hardcoded `authenticated = false`.

- [x] **3.3 Connect Pages to Backend API**
  - [x] Create an API utility layer (e.g. `dashboard/lib/api.ts`) to manage fetch requests with the Bearer JWT token attached.
  - [x] **Dashboard Feedbacks Page** ([dashboard/app/dashboard/page.tsx](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/dashboard/app/dashboard/page.tsx)):
    - Fetch active submissions from `GET /api/feedback`.
  - [x] **Projects Page** ([dashboard/app/projects/page.tsx](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/dashboard/app/projects/page.tsx)):
    - Fetch actual user projects using `GET /api/projects`.
  - [x] **Project Creation Page** ([dashboard/app/projects/create/page.tsx](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/dashboard/app/projects/create/page.tsx)):
    - Post the project data to `POST /api/projects`.
  - [x] **Settings Page** ([dashboard/app/settings/page.tsx](file:///home/jaison/code/projects/pingback/dashboard/app/settings/page.tsx)):
    - Load real profile information and configure settings (e.g., webhook urls).

