## 📦 Phase 4: Widget Script (`widget.js`) Implementation

A public-facing lightweight script needs to be written to render the feedback widget on client websites.

- [x] **4.1 Create Widget JS Script**
  - [x] Write a vanilla JS file (`widget.js`) to be hosted/served.
  - [x] The script should read parameters like `data-widget-id` from its own `<script>` tag.
  - [x] Fetch configuration from `GET /api/widgets/{widgetId}` to retrieve color theme (`PrimaryColor`), active fields (`Fields`), and UI templates.
  - [x] Inject a floating button into the client website body.
  - [x] On button click, open a sleek, responsive iframe or floating shadow-DOM container with the feedback form.
  - [x] Handle input validation, dynamic field rendering (e.g., email, text rating, feedback message).
  - [x] Submit payload via `POST /api/feedback` and display a success checkmark message.

